==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/lɪm.ɪts/}}
* {{audio|en-us-limit.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪmɪt|-ɪmɪt]]

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To restrict; not to allow to go beyond a certain bound.
#: ''We need to limit the power of the executive.''
#: ''I'm limiting myself to two drinks tonight.''

====Synonyms====
*(''restrict''): [[cap]], [[restrict]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[rajoittaa]]

===Noun===
'''limit''' (''plural:'' '''[[limits]]''')
# A restriction; a bound beyond which one may not go.
#: ''There are several existing limits to executive power.''
#: ''Two drinks is my limit tonight.''
# {{math}} A value to which a [[sequence]] [[converge]]s.
#: ''The sequence of reciprocals has zero as its limit.''
# {{math}} Any of several abstractions of this concept of limit.
#: ''Category theory defines a very general concept of limit.''

====Synonyms====
*(''restriction''): [[bound]], [[boundary]], [[limitation]], [[restriction]]

